    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Describes the culture, periods and styles of northern and central India under the Mughal emperors from the mid-16th to the late 17th century. Hallmarks of the period are a revival of Islamic architecture, and the mingling of Persian and indigenous Indian influence.</Note_Text>
